<TITLE> 2 Aug 21 'perpetrators' arrested </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  Police Tuesday arrested two people in Mohammadpur in the capital, who they say were militants with suspected links to the August 21, 2004 grenade attack on an Awami League rally. The arrestees, Maulana Md Monir Hossain, 35, and Maulana Md Idris, 40, were picked up from 21 Zakir Hossain Road by the Mohammadpur police. Shibli Noman, Mohammadpur police chief, told bdnews24.com, "Allegations are there that the two were involved in the August 21 grenade attack. It's also alleged that Maulana Md Monir Hossain was in touch with Mufti Hannan." (Details to follow) bdnews24
